    "The models were run locally with 4-bit quantization on a single A6000 GPU and prompted at a sampling temperature of 0.",
    "Results, summarized in Table 3, indicate that CoT prompting enhanced performance on average by 5.1%, 5.4%, and 8.9% on the area, delay, and static power metrics respectively.",
    "Supervised Fine-tuning (SFT)While few-shot prompting can help extrapolate LLM knowledge to new tasks, it is limited by how many examples we can fit in the context window and does not intrinsically instill knowledge in the LLM weights.",
    "Supervised fine-tuning (SFT) can help align the LLM to a specific downstream task by adjusting the LLM weights according to an instruction dataset.",
    "Therefore, we conduct extensive experiments on supervised fine-tuning."
